<?xml version="1.0"?>
<section xml:id="test-cases_testing-optional-parameters">
  <title>Testing Optional Parameters</title>
  <p>If a function takes an optional parameter, one of the edge cases to test for is when no parameter value is supplied
            during execution. Below are some tests for the built-in sorted function.</p>
  <program xml:id="ac19_2_3" interactive="activecode" language="python">
    <input>
assert sorted([1, 7, 4]) == [1, 4, 7]
assert sorted([1, 7, 4], reverse=True) == [7, 4, 1]
        </input>
  </program>
</section>
